(160, 12, 'JavaScript is a', 'JavaScript es un', 'JavaScript is a popular programming language used for web development.\r\nYou can use let to declare a variable that may change later.\r\nIf you use const, the value cannot be changed.\r\nTo show a message on the screen, use console.log(\"Hello World\");.\r\nFunctions are blocks of code that perform a task.\r\nA function can be declared with the keyword function.\r\nExample: function greet(name) { return \"Hello \" + name; }\r\nYou can call a function like this: greet(\"Anna\");.\r\nUse if to run code only if a condition is true.\r\nif (x > 10) { console.log(\"x is greater than 10\"); }\r\nYou can also use else or else if for other cases.\r\nArrays store multiple values in one variable.\r\nExample: let colors = [\"red\", \"blue\", \"green\"];\r\nAccess array items by index: colors[0] is \"red\".\r\nUse a for loop to repeat code a number of times.\r\nExample: for (let i = 0; i < 5; i++) { console.log(i); }\r\nObjects are collections of key-value pairs.\r\nExample: let user = { name: \"Ana\", age: 30 };\r\nAccess object data with dot notation: user.name.\r\nEvents are actions like clicks or key presses.\r\nYou can add an event listener with addEventListener.\r\nExample: button.addEventListener(\"click\", function() { alert(\"Clicked!\"); });\r\nArrow functions are a shorter way to write functions.\r\nExample: let sum = (a, b) => a + b;\r\nJavaScript is used to make websites interactive and dynamic.\r\nIt runs in the browser without needing to refresh the page.', '[{\"content\":\"JavaScript is a popular programming language used for web development.\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript es un lenguaje de programaci\\u00f3n popular utilizado para el desarrollo web.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 12:59:42\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript is a popular programming language used for web development.\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript es un lenguaje de programaci\\u00f3n popular utilizado para el desarrollo web.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 1