-11-03 16:30:19\"},{\"content\":\"Events are actions like clicks or key presses.\",\"translation\":\"Los eventos son acciones como clics o pulsaciones de teclas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:24\"},{\"content\":\"You can add an event listener with addEventListener.\",\"translation\":\"Puedes a\\u00f1adir un receptor de eventos con addEventListener.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:28\"},{\"content\":\"Example: button.addEventListener(\\\"click\\\", function() { alert(\\\"Clicked!\\\"); });\",\"translation\":\"Ejemplo: button.addEventListener(\\\"click\\\", function() { alert(\\\"\\u00a1Hecho clic!\\\"); });\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:31\"},{\"content\":\"Arrow functions are a shorter way to write functions.\",\"translation\":\"Las funciones de flecha son una forma m\\u00e1s corta de escribir funciones.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:39\"},{\"content\":\"Example: let sum = (a, b) => a + b;\",\"translation\":\"Ejemplo: que suma = (a, b) => a + b;\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:42\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript is used to make websites interactive and dynamic.\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript se utiliza para hacer que los sitios web sean interactivos y din\\u00e1micos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:49\"},{\"content\":\"It runs in the browser without needing to refresh the page.\",\"translation\":\"Se ejecuta en el navegador sin necesidad de actualizar la p\\u00e1gina.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-11-03 16:30:54\"}]', 0, NULL, '2025-07-25 18:08:22'),
(162, 12, 'JavaScript Array Methods', 'Métodos de matriz de JavaScript', 'JavaScript Array Methods List with English Descriptions\r\n\r\nBasic array methods\r\n\r\npush adds an element to the end of the array\r\npop removes the last element from the array\r\nunshift adds an element to the beginning of the array\r\nshift removes the first element from the array\r\nconcat combines two or more arrays into one\r\njoin joins all elements of the array into a string\r\nslice returns a portion of the array without modifying it\r\nsplice adds removes or replaces elements in the array modifying the original\r\nindexOf returns the index of the first matching element\r\nlastIndexOf returns the index of the last matching element\r\nincludes checks if an array contains a specific element\r\nreverse reverses the order of the elements in the array\r\nsort sorts the elements in the array alphabetically or numerically\r\n\r\nIteration and transformation methods\r\n\r\nforEach executes a function once for each array element\r\nmap creates a new array by applying a function to each element\r\nfilter creates a new array with elements that pass a test\r\nfind returns the first element that satisfies a test function\r\nfindIndex returns the index of the first element that satisfies a test\r\nevery returns true if all elements pass a test\r\nsome returns true if at least one element passes a test\r\nreduce applies a function to reduce the array to a single value\r\nflat flattens nested arrays into a single level array\r\nflatMap maps and then flattens the result into a new array\r\n\r\nAdditional useful methods\r\n\r\nfill fills all or part of the array with a static value\r\ncopyWithin copies part of the array to another location in the same array\r\nat returns the element at a specific index supports negative indexing\r\ntoString converts the array to a string\r\nArray isArray checks whether a variable is an array\r\n\r\nJavaScript Functions\r\n\r\nFunctions are reusable blocks of code that perform a task\r\n\r\nFunction declaration example\r\n\r\nfunction greet name returns Hello followed by the name\r\n\r\nArrow functions\r\n\r\nArrow functions are a shorter syntax for writing functions\r\n\r\nExample of arrow function that adds two numbers\r\n\r\nconst add equals open parenthesis a comma b close parenthesis arrow a plus b\r\n\r\nIf the function has only one parameter you can omit the parentheses\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nconst square equals x arrow x times x\r\n\r\nArrow functions are useful for callbacks and concise code\r\n\r\nJavaScript Variables\r\n\r\nVariables store data values\r\n\r\nYou can declare variables using var let or const\r\n\r\nLet is block scoped and preferred over var\r\n\r\nConst is used for constants that do not change\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nlet count equals 0\r\n\r\nconst pi equals 3 point 1416\r\n\r\nYou can update let variables but not const variables\r\n\r\nJavaScript Conditionals\r\n\r\nConditional statements allow decision making in code\r\n\r\nIf statement runs code if a condition is true\r\n\r\nElse runs code if the condition is false\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nif count greater than 10 open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log Count is greater than ten\r\n\r\nclose brace else open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log Count is ten or less\r\n\r\nclose brace\r\n\r\nJavaScript Loops\r\n\r\nLoops repeat code multiple times\r\n\r\nFor loop runs code a fixed number of times\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nfor let i equals zero semicolon i less than five semicolon i plus plus open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log i\r\n\r\nclose brace\r\n\r\nWhile loop runs code while a condition is true\r\n\r\nExample\r\n\r\nwhile count less than five open brace\r\n\r\nconsole dot log count\r\n\r\ncount plus plus\r\n\r\nclose brace', '[{\"content\":\"JavaScript Array Methods List with English Descriptions\",\"translation\":\"Lista de m\\u00e9todos de matrices de JavaScript con descripciones en ingl\\u00e9s\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:05\"},{\"content\":\"Basic array methods\",\"translation\":\"M\\u00e9todos b\\u00e1sicos de array\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:16\"},{\"content\":\"push adds an element to the end of the array\",\"translation\":\"push a\\u00f1ade un elemento al final de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:22\"},{\"content\":\"pop removes the last element from the array\",\"translation\":\"pop elimina el \\u00faltimo elemento de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:30\"},{\"content\":\"unshift adds an element to the beginning of the array\",\"translation\":\"unshift a\\u00f1ade un elemento al principio de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:38\"},{\"content\":\"shift removes the first element from the array\",\"translation\":\"shift elimina el primer elemento de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:32:52\"},{\"content\":\"concat combines two or more arrays into one\",\"translation\":\"concat combina dos o m\\u00e1s matrices en una sola\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:00\"},{\"content\":\"join joins all elements of the array into a string\",\"translation\":\"join une todos los elementos de la matriz en una cadena\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:10\"},{\"content\":\"slice returns a portion of the array without modifying it\",\"translation\":\"slice devuelve una parte de la matriz sin modificarla\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:25\"},{\"content\":\"splice adds removes or replaces elements in the array modifying the original\",\"translation\":\"splice a\\u00f1ade, elimina o sustituye elementos en el array modificando el original\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:36\"},{\"content\":\"indexOf returns the index of the first matching element\",\"translation\":\"indexOf devuelve el \\u00edndice del primer elemento coincidente\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:44\"},{\"content\":\"lastIndexOf returns the index of the last matching element\",\"translation\":\"lastIndexOf devuelve el \\u00edndice del \\u00faltimo elemento coincidente\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:33:59\"},{\"content\":\"includes checks if an array contains a specific element\",\"translation\":\"incluye la comprobaci\\u00f3n de si una matriz contiene un elemento espec\\u00edfico\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:16\"},{\"content\":\"reverse reverses the order of the elements in the array\",\"translation\":\"reverse invierte el orden de los elementos de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:16\"},{\"content\":\"sort sorts the elements in the array alphabetically or numerically\",\"translation\":\"sort ordena los elementos de la matriz alfab\\u00e9tica o num\\u00e9ricamente\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:19\"},{\"content\":\"Iteration and transformation methods\",\"translation\":\"M\\u00e9todos de iteraci\\u00f3n y transformaci\\u00f3n\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:31\"},{\"content\":\"forEach executes a function once for each array element\",\"translation\":\"forEach ejecuta una funci\\u00f3n una vez por cada elemento de la matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:42\"},{\"content\":\"map creates a new array by applying a function to each element\",\"translation\":\"map crea una nueva matriz aplicando una funci\\u00f3n a cada elemento\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:34:58\"},{\"content\":\"filter creates a new array with elements that pass a test\",\"translation\":\"crea una nueva matriz con los elementos que superan una prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:08\"},{\"content\":\"find returns the first element that satisfies a test function\",\"translation\":\"find devuelve el primer elemento que satisface una funci\\u00f3n de prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:18\"},{\"content\":\"findIndex returns the index of the first element that satisfies a test\",\"translation\":\"findIndex devuelve el \\u00edndice del primer elemento que satisface una prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:35\"},{\"content\":\"every returns true if all elements pass a test\",\"translation\":\"every devuelve verdadero si todos los elementos superan una prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:35\"},{\"content\":\"some returns true if at least one element passes a test\",\"translation\":\"some devuelve verdadero si al menos un elemento supera una prueba\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:39\"},{\"content\":\"reduce applies a function to reduce the array to a single value\",\"translation\":\"reduce aplica una funci\\u00f3n para reducir la matriz a un \\u00fanico valor\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:35:48\"},{\"content\":\"flat flattens nested arrays into a single level array\",\"translation\":\"flat aplana las matrices anidadas en una matriz de un solo nivel\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:36:01\"},{\"content\":\"flatMap maps and then flattens the result into a new array\",\"translation\":\"flatMap mapea y luego aplana el resultado en una nueva matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:36:16\"},{\"content\":\"Additional useful methods\",\"translation\":\"Otros m\\u00e9todos \\u00fatiles\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:36:28\"},{\"content\":\"fill fills all or part of the array with a static value\",\"translation\":\"fill rellena todo o parte del array con un valor est\\u00e1tico\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:36:34\"},{\"content\":\"copyWithin copies part of the array to another location in the same array\",\"translation\":\"copyWithin copia parte de la matriz en otra ubicaci\\u00f3n de la misma matriz\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:36:45\"},{\"content\":\"at returns the element at a specific index supports negative indexing\",\"translation\":\"at devuelve el elemento en un \\u00edndice espec\\u00edfico admite indexaci\\u00f3n negativa\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:02\"},{\"content\":\"toString converts the array to a string\",\"translation\":\"toString convierte la matriz en una cadena\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:08\"},{\"content\":\"Array isArray checks whether a variable is an array\",\"translation\":\"Array isArray comprueba si una variable es un array\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:12\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript Functions\",\"translation\":\"Funciones de JavaScript\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:27\"},{\"content\":\"Functions are reusable blocks of code that perform a task\",\"translation\":\"Las funciones son bloques de c\\u00f3digo reutilizables que realizan una tarea\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:32\"},{\"content\":\"Function declaration example\",\"translation\":\"Ejemplo de declaraci\\u00f3n de funci\\u00f3n\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:43\"},{\"content\":\"function greet name returns Hello followed by the name\",\"translation\":\"La funci\\u00f3n greet name devuelve Hello seguido del nombre\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:50\"},{\"content\":\"Arrow functions\",\"translation\":\"Funciones de flecha\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:53\"},{\"content\":\"Arrow functions are a shorter syntax for writing functions\",\"translation\":\"Las funciones en flecha son una sintaxis m\\u00e1s corta para escribir funciones\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:37:58\"},{\"content\":\"Example of arrow function that adds two numbers\",\"translation\":\"Ejemplo de funci\\u00f3n de flecha que suma dos n\\u00fameros\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:38:13\"},{\"content\":\"const add equals open parenthesis a comma b close parenthesis arrow a plus b\",\"translation\":\"const add equals par\\u00e9ntesis abierto a coma b par\\u00e9ntesis cerrado flecha a m\\u00e1s b\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:38:22\"},{\"content\":\"If the function has only one parameter you can omit the parentheses\",\"translation\":\"Si la funci\\u00f3n s\\u00f3lo tiene un par\\u00e1metro, puede omitir los par\\u00e9ntesis\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:38:39\"},{\"content\":\"Example\",\"translation\":\"Ejemplo\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:38:51\"},{\"content\":\"const square equals x arrow x times x\",\"translation\":\"const cuadrado es igual a x flecha x veces x\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:38:55\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript Variables\",\"translation\":\"JavaScript Variables\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:05\"},{\"content\":\"Arrow functions are useful for callbacks and concise code\",\"translation\":\"Las funciones de flecha son \\u00fatiles para las retrollamadas y el c\\u00f3digo conciso\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:05\"},{\"content\":\"Variables store data values\",\"translation\":\"Las variables almacenan valores de datos\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:11\"},{\"content\":\"You can declare variables using var let or const\",\"translation\":\"Puedes declarar variables utilizando var let o const\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:18\"},{\"content\":\"Let is block scoped and preferred over var\",\"translation\":\"Let tiene alcance de bloque y es preferible a var\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:29\"},{\"content\":\"Const is used for constants that do not change\",\"translation\":\"Const se utiliza para constantes que no cambian\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:37\"},{\"content\":\"let count equals 0\",\"translation\":\"let count igual a 0\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:50\"},{\"content\":\"const pi equals 3 point 1416\",\"translation\":\"const pi igual a 3 punto 1416\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:39:56\"},{\"content\":\"You can update let variables but not const variables\",\"translation\":\"Puedes actualizar variables let pero no variables const\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:40:06\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript Conditionals\",\"translation\":\"Condicionales de JavaScript\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:40:16\"},{\"content\":\"Conditional statements allow decision making in code\",\"translation\":\"Las sentencias condicionales permiten tomar decisiones en el c\\u00f3digo\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:40:22\"},{\"content\":\"If statement runs code if a condition is true\",\"translation\":\"La sentencia If ejecuta el c\\u00f3digo si una condici\\u00f3n es verdadera\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:40:32\"},{\"content\":\"Else runs code if the condition is false\",\"translation\":\"Else ejecuta el c\\u00f3digo si la condici\\u00f3n es falsa\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:40:40\"},{\"content\":\"if count greater than 10 open brace\",\"translation\":\"si el recuento es superior a 10 abrir el corchete\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:40:53\"},{\"content\":\"console dot log Count is greater than ten\",\"translation\":\"console dot log La cuenta es mayor que diez\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:01\"},{\"content\":\"close brace else open brace\",\"translation\":\"cerrar corchete si no abrir corchete\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:14\"},{\"content\":\"console dot log Count is ten or less\",\"translation\":\"console dot log La cuenta es diez o menos\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:21\"},{\"content\":\"close brace\",\"translation\":\"tirante cerrado\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:29\"},{\"content\":\"JavaScript Loops\",\"translation\":\"Bucles JavaScript\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:34\"},{\"content\":\"Loops repeat code multiple times\",\"translation\":\"Los bucles repiten el c\\u00f3digo varias veces\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:39\"},{\"content\":\"For loop runs code a fixed number of times\",\"translation\":\"El bucle For ejecuta el c\\u00f3digo un n\\u00famero fijo de veces\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:41:47\"},{\"content\":\"for let i equals zero semicolon i less than five semicolon i plus plus open brace\",\"translation\":\"for let i igual a cero punto y coma i menor que cinco punto y coma i m\\u00e1s m\\u00e1s llave abierta\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:42:00\"},{\"content\":\"console dot log i\",\"translation\":\"consola punto log i\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:42:08\"},{\"content\":\"While loop runs code while a condition is true\",\"translation\":\"El bucle while ejecuta c\\u00f3digo mientras una condici\\u00f3n es verdadera\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:42:15\"},{\"content\":\"while count less than five open brace\",\"translation\":\"mientras cuente menos de cinco llaves abiertas\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:42:27\"},{\"content\":\"console dot log count\",\"translation\":\"console dot log count\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:42:34\"},{\"content\":\"count plus plus\",\"translation\":\"contar m\\u00e1s m\\u00e1s\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-08 03:42:40\"}]', 0, NULL, '2025-08-06 07:12:45');
