(164, 12, 'Understanding Grammar Differences', 'Comprender las diferencias de gramática', 'Understanding Grammar Differences\r\n\r\nEnglish grammar often places adjectives before nouns, while Spanish usually puts them after the nouns.\r\nIn Spanish, verbs change endings to indicate subject and tense, unlike English, which often uses auxiliary verbs.\r\nEnglish pronouns rarely change form except for subject and object cases, but Spanish pronouns vary much more.\r\nArticles in English stay the same regardless of gender, while Spanish articles change for masculine and feminine.\r\nIn English, the word order is important for meaning, but Spanish allows more flexibility in sentence structure.\r\nQuestions in English require auxiliary verbs, whereas Spanish can simply change intonation to form questions.\r\nEnglish uses “do” in questions and negatives, but Spanish expresses these without an extra auxiliary verb.\r\nIn Spanish, subject pronouns are often omitted because the verb form already shows who is acting.\r\nEnglish must always include the subject, except in imperatives, to make sentences grammatically correct.\r\nSpanish adjectives agree in gender and number with nouns, while English adjectives remain unchanged.\r\nIn English, prepositions are fixed in expressions, but Spanish sometimes changes prepositions depending on context.\r\nVerb tenses in English use auxiliary verbs like “have” or “will,” while Spanish modifies the verb endings directly.\r\nEnglish modal verbs never change form, but Spanish equivalent verbs conjugate according to subject and tense.\r\nPassive voice is more common in English, while Spanish prefers active voice or reflexive constructions.\r\nEnglish relies on word order for emphasis, whereas Spanish can use different structures to highlight information.\r\nBoth languages have unique ways of expressing ideas, and understanding these differences improves communication greatly.', '[{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:00\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:03\"},{\"content\":\"English grammar often places adjectives before nouns, while Spanish usually puts them after the nouns.\",\"translation\":\"La gram\\u00e1tica inglesa a menudo coloca adjetivos antes de los sustantivos, mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol generalmente los pone despu\\u00e9s de los sustantivos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:05\"},{\"content\":\"In Spanish, verbs change endings to indicate subject and tense, unlike English, which often uses auxiliary verbs.\",\"translation\":\"En espa\\u00f1ol, los verbos cambian las terminaciones para indicar sujeto y tiempo, a diferencia del ingl\\u00e9s, que a menudo usa verbos auxiliares.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:14\"},{\"content\":\"English pronouns rarely change form except for subject and object cases, but Spanish pronouns vary much more.\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres ingleses rara vez cambian la forma, excepto los casos de sujetos y objetos, pero los pronombres espa\\u00f1oles var\\u00edan mucho m\\u00e1s.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:25\"},{\"content\":\"Articles in English stay the same regardless of gender, while Spanish articles change for masculine and feminine.\",\"translation\":\"Los art\\u00edculos en ingl\\u00e9s permanecen igual independientemente del g\\u00e9nero, mientras que los art\\u00edculos espa\\u00f1oles cambian para masculinos y femeninos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:36\"},{\"content\":\"In English, the word order is important for meaning, but Spanish allows more flexibility in sentence structure.\",\"translation\":\"En ingl\\u00e9s, el orden de la palabra es importante para el significado, pero el espa\\u00f1ol permite m\\u00e1s flexibilidad en la estructura de las oraciones.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:46\"},{\"content\":\"Questions in English require auxiliary verbs, whereas Spanish can simply change intonation to form questions.\",\"translation\":\"Las preguntas en ingl\\u00e9s requieren verbos auxiliares, mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol simplemente puede cambiar la entonaci\\u00f3n para formar preguntas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 15:59:55\"},{\"content\":\"English uses \\u201cdo\\u201d in questions and negatives, but Spanish expresses these without an extra auxiliary verb.\",\"translation\":\"El ingl\\u00e9s usa \\\"hacer\\\" en preguntas y negativos, pero el espa\\u00f1ol los expresa sin un verbo auxiliar adicional.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:06\"},{\"content\":\"In Spanish, subject pronouns are often omitted because the verb form already shows who is acting.\",\"translation\":\"En espa\\u00f1ol, los pronombres de temas a menudo se omiten porque la forma verbal ya muestra qui\\u00e9n est\\u00e1 actuando.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:18\"},{\"content\":\"In Spanish, subject pronouns are often omitted because the verb form already shows who is acting.\",\"translation\":\"En espa\\u00f1ol, los pronombres de temas a menudo se omiten porque la forma verbal ya muestra qui\\u00e9n est\\u00e1 actuando.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:20\"},{\"content\":\"English must always include the subject, except in imperatives, to make sentences grammatically correct.\",\"translation\":\"El ingl\\u00e9s siempre debe incluir el sujeto, excepto en los imperativos, para hacer que las oraciones sean gramaticalmente correctas.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:27\"},{\"content\":\"Spanish adjectives agree in gender and number with nouns, while English adjectives remain unchanged.\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos espa\\u00f1oles est\\u00e1n de acuerdo en g\\u00e9nero y n\\u00famero con sustantivos, mientras que los adjetivos en ingl\\u00e9s permanecen sin cambios.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:36\"},{\"content\":\"In English, prepositions are fixed in expressions, but Spanish sometimes changes prepositions depending on context.\",\"translation\":\"En ingl\\u00e9s, las preposiciones se fijan en expresiones, pero el espa\\u00f1ol a veces cambia las preposiciones dependiendo del contexto.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:45\"},{\"content\":\"Verb tenses in English use auxiliary verbs like \\u201chave\\u201d or \\u201cwill,\\u201d while Spanish modifies the verb endings directly.\",\"translation\":\"Los tiempos verbales en ingl\\u00e9s usan verbos auxiliares como \\\"tener\\\" o \\\"voluntad\\\", mientras que el espa\\u00f1ol modifica las terminaciones verbales directamente.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:00:56\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:14:48\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias de gram\\u00e1tica\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-10 16:14:50\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:33:38\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:37:04\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:37:42\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 05:53:37\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 06:44:11\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-09-03 06:45:56\"},{\"content\":\"Understanding Grammar Differences\",\"translation\":\"Comprender las diferencias gramaticales\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-0