(166, 22, 'The Forgotten Library', 'La biblioteca olvidada', 'La biblioteca olvidada\r\nIn a quiet town, there stood an abandoned library.\r\nDust covered every book, and silence ruled the halls.\r\nPeople passed by daily, never daring to step inside.\r\n\r\nOne day, Clara, a curious student, noticed the locked door.\r\nHer love for literature made the place irresistible to explore.\r\nShe carried a lantern, trembling, yet eager to discover secrets.\r\n\r\nInside, the shelves leaned, tired from holding forgotten worlds.\r\nPages whispered faintly, as if longing for human company again.\r\nClara touched a novel, and suddenly the air shifted.\r\n\r\nThe library awakened, glowing softly under her cautious steps.\r\nCharacters walked from books, murmuring fragments of lost stories.\r\nShakespearean heroes greeted her, Dickensâ€™ ghosts sang of forgotten streets.\r\n\r\nClara realized she wasnâ€™t just reading, she was inside.\r\nThe library became alive because someone cared to listen.\r\nEvery story she touched rebuilt the crumbling walls of memory.\r\n\r\nNight after night, she returned, restoring the libraryâ€™s fading strength.\r\nHer classmates laughed, believing she wasted time on old books.\r\nBut Clara knew she wasnâ€™t saving books; they saved her.\r\n\r\nThrough stories, she found courage, wisdom, and a thousand voices.\r\nThe library, once forgotten, became her most loyal companion.\r\nLiterature proved itself timeless, breathing through whoever dares to read.', '[{\"content\":\"In a quiet town, there stood an abandoned library.\",\"translation\":\"En un pueblo tranquilo, hab\\u00eda una biblioteca abandonada.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:30:22\"},{\"content\":\"Dust covered every book, and silence ruled the halls.\",\"translation\":\"El polvo cubr\\u00eda todos los libros y el silencio reinaba en los pasillos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-20 13:30:27\"},{\"content\":\"In a quiet town, there stood an abandoned library.\",\"translation\":\"En un pueblo tranqui