(167, 22, 'The Journey of Words', 'El viaje de las palabras', 'The Journey of Words\r\nEthan loved books more than anything in the world.\r\nHis suitcase was never clothes, but always full of novels.\r\nHe believed every journey began with reading, not with maps.\r\n\r\nOne summer, he boarded a train across distant green valleys.\r\nThe rhythm of wheels echoed like verses on old paper.\r\nHe opened Homer, and seas rose beyond the train window.\r\n\r\nMountains became Troyâ€™s walls, and fellow travelers looked like warriors.\r\nEach station felt like a new chapter waiting to unfold.\r\nThe world outside and inside his book merged into one.\r\n\r\nIn Italy, he carried Dante beneath Florenceâ€™s burning sunsets.\r\nEvery bridge whispered lines about exile, love, and redemption.\r\nHe recited softly, and the river replied with echoes.\r\n\r\nIn Spain, Don Quixote rode alongside buses and wandering tourists.\r\nWindmills near La Mancha turned like giants in slow dance.\r\nEthan laughed, certain literature had painted reality with bold colors.\r\n\r\nWeeks passed, and his journey stitched stories into living memory.\r\nNo city existed without a book to explain it.\r\nNo word lived unless a traveler carried it further.\r\n\r\nWhen he returned home, people asked what countries he visited.\r\nHe smiled: â€œI traveled through books, and books traveled through me.â€\r\nFor Ethan, every journey was literature, and literature was travel.', '[{\"content\":\"Ethan loved books more than anything in the world.\",\"translation\":\"Ethan amaba los libros m\\u00e1s que a nada en el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:34:30\"},{\"content\":\"Ethan loved books more than anything in the world.\",\"translation\":\"Ethan amaba los libros m\\u00e1s que a nada en el mundo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-25 04:34:30\"},{\"content\":\"His suitcase was never clothes, but always full of novels.\",\"translation\":\"En su maleta nunca hab\\u00eda ropa, pero siempre estaba llena de novelas.\",\"time