(170, 22, 'Personal pronouns are', 'Los pronombres personales son', 'Personal pronouns are very common in English, and they replace nouns clearly.\r\nSubject pronouns include words like \"I, you, he, she, it, we, they\".\r\nObject pronouns are used after verbs or prepositions, like \"me, him, us\".\r\nFor example, instead of saying \"I see Maria\", we can simply say \"I see her\".\r\nPossessive adjectives show ownership, and they include \"my, your, his, her, our, their\".\r\nThese words modify a noun, for example: \"This is my book, not your notebook\".\r\nPossessive pronouns stand alone, without nouns, and they include \"mine, yours, hers, theirs\".\r\nFor example, we say: \"This pen is mine, but that computer is yours\".\r\nReflexive pronouns are used when the subject and the object are the same.\r\nThey include words like \"myself, yourself, himself, herself, itself, ourselves, yourselves, themselves\".\r\nFor example: \"She taught herself Spanish because she wanted to travel and study abroad\".\r\nDemonstrative pronouns point to things: \"this, that, these, those\" are the common forms.\r\nWe use them to show objects near or far, singular or plural in context.\r\nIndefinite pronouns do not refer to specific people or things, like \"someone, anyone, everything, nothing\".\r\nCorrect use of pronouns improves clarity and avoids repetition in everyday English communication.', '[{\"content\":\"Personal pronouns are very common in English, and they replace nouns clearly.\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres personales son muy comunes en ingl\\u00e9s y sustituyen claramente a los sustantivos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:55:42\"},{\"content\":\"Personal pronouns are very common in English, and they replace nouns clearly.\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres personales son muy comunes en ingl\\u00e9s y sustituyen claramente a los sustantivos.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:55:43\"},{\"content\":\"Subject pronouns include words like \\\"I, you, he, she, it, we, they\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres sujeto incluyen palabras como \\\"yo, t\\u00fa, \\u00e9l, ella, ello, nosotros, ellos\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:55:58\"},{\"content\":\"Object pronouns are used after verbs or prepositions, like \\\"me, him, us\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres de objetos se usan despu\\u00e9s de verbos o preposiciones, como \\\"yo, \\u00e9l, nosotros\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:56:48\"},{\"content\":\"For example, instead of saying \\\"I see Maria\\\", we can simply say \\\"I see her\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Por ejemplo, en lugar de decir \\\"veo a Mar\\u00eda\\\", podemos decir simplemente \\\"la veo\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:56:59\"},{\"content\":\"Possessive adjectives show ownership, and they include \\\"my, your, his, her, our, their\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los adjetivos posesivos muestran propiedad, e incluyen \\\"mi, tu, su, su, nuestro, su\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:57:17\"},{\"content\":\"These words modify a noun, for example: \\\"This is my book, not your notebook\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Estas palabras modifican a un sustantivo, por ejemplo: \\\"Este es mi libro, no tu cuaderno\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:57:37\"},{\"content\":\"Possessive pronouns stand alone, without nouns, and they include \\\"mine, yours, hers, theirs\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres posesivos van solos, sin sustantivos, e incluyen \\\"m\\u00edo, tuyo, suyo, de ellos\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:57:53\"},{\"content\":\"For example, we say: \\\"This pen is mine, but that computer is yours\\\".\",\"translation\":\"Por ejemplo, decimos: \\\"Este bol\\u00edgrafo es m\\u00edo, pero ese ordenador es tuyo\\\".\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:58:13\"},{\"content\":\"Reflexive pronouns are used when the subject and the object are the same.\",\"translation\":\"Los pronombres reflexivos se utilizan cuando el sujeto y el objeto son el mismo.\",\"timestamp\":\"2025-08-28 11:58:29\"},{\"content\":\"They in